role.name: role
role.description: The role of this MCB in the management hierarchy.

systemDateAndTime.name: systemDateAndTime
systemDateAndTime.description: Current time as set on system realtime clock. Also allows system realtime clock to be set.

networkTimeServer1.name: networkTimeServer1
networkTimeServer1.description: IP address of the time server to be used.

networkTimeProtocol.name: networkTimeProtocol
networkTimeProtocol.description: Protocol to use when with network time server.

networkTimeEnable.name: networkTimeEnable
networkTimeEnable.description: Enable/disabled the use of a network time server.

managementMibVersion.name: managementMibVersion
managementMibVersion.description: Version of the ADIC-MANAGEMENT-MIB on which this agent is based.

enableDaylightSavingsTime.name: enableDaylightSavingsTime
enableDaylightSavingsTime.description: Enable automatic adjustment of the system date and time for daylight savings time.

networkTimeServer2.name: networkTimeServer2
networkTimeServer2.description: IP address of the second time server to be used. Multiple time servers may be used for redundancy and (or) improved time accuracy.

globalEthernetTable.name: globalEthernetTable
globalEthernetTable.description: Some Ethernet settings/switches. Routing tables are part of MIB-II, so we don't include them here.

ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: IP Address of this MCB's external Ethernet port.

ipAddressSubnetMask.name: ipAddressSubnetMask
ipAddressSubnetMask.description: Read-Write version of MIB-II ipAdEntNetMask Object. ** Description clause from MIB-II text ** The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

preferredSpeed.name: preferredSpeed
preferredSpeed.description: The preferred Ethernet speed for this Ethernet port.

actualSpeed.name: actualSpeed
actualSpeed.description: The actual (negotiated) speed for this Ethernet port.

ethernetDuplex.name: ethernetDuplex
ethernetDuplex.description: The duplex setting for this Ethernet port.

systemManagerEntry.name: systemManagerEntry
systemManagerEntry.description: The MCB System Manager (MSM) provides the high level system management of the MCB. The primary role of the MSM is to configure, initialize, and maintain the software processes running on the MCB.

softwareComponentIndex.name: softwareComponentIndex
softwareComponentIndex.description: Identifies which piece of MCB software is being addressed.

processRowStatus.name: processRowStatus
processRowStatus.description: Row status object for creating/deleting system components.

processPhysicalMemory.name: processPhysicalMemory
processPhysicalMemory.description: The size in kilobytes of the actual software process binary.

processResidentMemory.name: processResidentMemory
processResidentMemory.description: The size in kilobytes of the software process portion that is currently resident in memory.

softwareInstallationTable.name: softwareInstallationTable
softwareInstallationTable.description: This table controls installation of software packages/updates.

installPackageName.name: installPackageName
installPackageName.description: Filename and path of the package to be installed. The management application writes the filename here, which initiates the update process.

installProcessStatus.name: installProcessStatus
installProcessStatus.description: ok - installation successful - this is the intial state inProgress - software package in being installed failed - software package installation failed. The status should return failed until another write to installPackageFilename. updateAborted - software installation was cancel and system reverts back to previous version

installCommand.name: installCommand
installCommand.description: download - copy firmware bundle to MCB but do not install install - commence installation (could be current bundle or previously downloaded bundle) abort - abort installation in progress rollback - rollback to the previous version of the system identified by the value in the previousFirmwareVersion field. timeEstimate - provides a estimate on the overall download time for a previously downloaded bundle

installStatusText.name: installStatusText
installStatusText.description: Indicates time to complete the entire installation: example: Estimated time to complete download xx minutes

currentFirmwareVersion.name: currentFirmwareVersion
currentFirmwareVersion.description: Firmware revision currently on the i2000.

previousFirmwareVersion.name: previousFirmwareVersion
previousFirmwareVersion.description: Previous firmware revision on the i2000 that is available for rollback.

downloadedFirmwareVersion.name: downloadedFirmwareVersion
downloadedFirmwareVersion.description: Identifier for a the bundle that was previously downloaded to the i2000 but not installed.

componentsInBundle.name: componentsInBundle
componentsInBundle.description: Identifies the components being installed with this bundle ********************************************************** (LSB) bit 0 - MCB bit 1 - CMB bit 2 - RCU bit 3 - FCB bit 4 - AMC

mcbInstallStatusText.name: mcbInstallStatusText
mcbInstallStatusText.description: Provides detailed information about the MCB component install Example: download status (inprogress, complete, failed, not being upgraded) : current component : time to complete MCB

cmbInstallStatusText.name: cmbInstallStatusText
cmbInstallStatusText.description: Provides detailed information about the CMB component install Example: download status (inprogress, complete, failed, not being upgraded) : current CMB : time to complete CMB/s

rcuInstallStatusText.name: rcuInstallStatusText
rcuInstallStatusText.description: Provides detailed information about the RCU component install Example: download status (inprogress, complete, failed, not being upgraded) : current component : time to complete RCU

fcbInstallStatusText.name: fcbInstallStatusText
fcbInstallStatusText.description: Provides detailed information about the FCB component install Example: download status (inprogress, complete, failed, not being upgraded) : current fcb : time to complete FCB/s

amcInstallStatusText.name: amcInstallStatusText
amcInstallStatusText.description: Provides detailed information about the AMC component install Example: download status (inprogress, complete, failed, not being upgraded) : current component : time to complete AMC

capacity.name: capacity
capacity.description: The number of kilobytes of file space on this MCB.

freeSpace.name: freeSpace
freeSpace.description: The number of kilobytes of availble (unused) file space on this MCB.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: ** This object is obsolete. ** User's name.

userRowStatus.name: userRowStatus
userRowStatus.description: ** This object is obsolete. ** Standard Row Status object. Used primarily to delete users.

userGroup.name: userGroup
userGroup.description: ** This object is obsolete. ** User's group.

userPassword.name: userPassword
userPassword.description: ** This object is obsolete. ** User's password.

userLibAccessList.name: userLibAccessList
userLibAccessList.description: ** This object is obsolete. ** Delimited list of logical library identifiers to which this use has access.

licenseKeyIndex.name: licenseKeyIndex
licenseKeyIndex.description: Ordinal inde for this table. Identifies a license key database entry. Each key may enable multiple features. A list of features enabled by each key can be found in the licenseFeatureTable.

licenseKeyRowStatus.name: licenseKeyRowStatus
licenseKeyRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of rows in the license key database.

licenseKeyDuration.name: licenseKeyDuration
licenseKeyDuration.description: Is this license key permanent or transient? Permanent keys have no expiration date, transient keys expire at the time found in the licenseKeyExpirationDate object.

licenseKeyExpirationDate.name: licenseKeyExpirationDate
licenseKeyExpirationDate.description: Exact date and time when this license key expires. Has no meaning if license key is permanent.

licenseKeyAppliedDate.name: licenseKeyAppliedDate
licenseKeyAppliedDate.description: Date and time when the license key was applied. This field indicates the chronological order in which the keys were applied. If multiple keys enable the same feature, the most recent key supercedes older keys.

licenseFeatureTable.name: licenseFeatureTable
licenseFeatureTable.description: This table is a list of all features activated by a particular license key.

licenseFeatureIndex.name: licenseFeatureIndex
licenseFeatureIndex.description: Feature index for this table, as well as licensable feature table. If a feature is not licensed, the row corresponding to that feature does not appear here, but it does appear in the licensableFeatureTable, as do all licensableFeatures.

featureName.name: featureName
featureName.description: Name of the ADIC licensed feature enable by this row's license key. The key is specified by the value of licenseKeyIndex.

licenseFeatureQuantity.name: licenseFeatureQuantity
licenseFeatureQuantity.description: The quantity of this licensed feature enabled by this license key, if applicable. For example, a license key which enables 1000 slots of Capacity-on-Demand storage would have quantity = 1000. For features which are not licensed by quantity, return 0.

licensableFeatureTable.name: licensableFeatureTable
licensableFeatureTable.description: This table is a list of all licensable features. It defines the mapping between a feature name and its licenseFeatureIndex.

licensableFeatureName.name: licensableFeatureName
licensableFeatureName.description: Name of the ADIC licensable feature to be displayed to the user.

totalQuantityLicensed.name: totalQuantityLicensed
totalQuantityLicensed.description: The total licensed quantity for this feature. For features which are licensed by quantity, this object returns the sum of the indiviual quantities enabled by each license key (see licenseFeatureQuantity). For example, if there were two COD license keys installed, one for 500 slots and one for 1000 slots, totalQuantityLicensed would return 1500.

hostIpAddress.name: hostIpAddress
hostIpAddress.description: Host IP address to which SNMP traps will be sent/forwarded.

udpPort.name: udpPort
udpPort.description: UDP Port number on which to send/forward SNMP traps.

registrationRowStatus.name: registrationRowStatus
registrationRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of rows in the notification (trap registration) table.

logTable.name: logTable
logTable.description: ** This table is optional ** Management functionality for general event logging. Log entries are not necessarily available via SNMP.

logName.name: logName
logName.description: ** This object is optional. ** Name of the log to be accessed.

logSnapshotTable.name: logSnapshotTable
logSnapshotTable.description: ** This table is optional. ** Management functionality for generating a snapshot archive containing all of the system logs

logSnapshotCommand.name: logSnapshotCommand
logSnapshotCommand.description: ** This object is optional. ** Commands are: ********************** retrieveLogs - Gather snapshots of various system logs in preparation to build snapshot archive file.

numElementDomains.name: numElementDomains
numElementDomains.description: Number of element domains (such as DLT, LTO, 8mm, etc.) currently installed in this physical library.

numPhAisles.name: numPhAisles
numPhAisles.description: Number of aisles in this library.

operatingMode.name: operatingMode
operatingMode.description: Controls library behavior when retrieving tape from drives.

numStorageCartridges.name: numStorageCartridges
numStorageCartridges.description: Total number of storage cartridges present in the library

numCleaningCartridges.name: numCleaningCartridges
numCleaningCartridges.description: Total number of cleaning cartridges present in the library

physLibraryManagerLun.name: physLibraryManagerLun
physLibraryManagerLun.description: The SCSI logical unit number of the Physical Library Manager.

physLibraryAutoCleaning.name: physLibraryAutoCleaning
physLibraryAutoCleaning.description: Enable/disable automatic drive cleaning for the entire physical library.

numPhFrames.name: numPhFrames
numPhFrames.description: The number of physical frames in the library.

totalRawCapacity.name: totalRawCapacity
totalRawCapacity.description: An estimate of the amount of data which the library can hold. Units are gigabytes. May be computed by multiplying the number of cells by the maximum number of gigabytes per tape.

totalFreeCapacity.name: totalFreeCapacity
totalFreeCapacity.description: An estimate of the unused data capacity of the library. Units are gigabytes. May be computed by multiplying the number of empty cells by the maximum number of gigabytes per tape.

totalUsedCapacity.name: totalUsedCapacity
totalUsedCapacity.description: An estimate of the used data capacity of the library. Units are gigabytes. May be computed by multiplying the number of full cells by the maximum number of gigabytes per tape.

logicalSNAdressingMode.name: logicalSNAdressingMode
logicalSNAdressingMode.description: Enables/disables the logical serial number addressing feature.

mediaDomainTable.name: mediaDomainTable
mediaDomainTable.description: Table of all media domains installed in the library.

numStorageElements.name: numStorageElements
numStorageElements.description: Total number of storage elements for this media domain in this physical library.

numIeElements.name: numIeElements
numIeElements.description: Total number of import/export elements for this media domain in this physical library.

numCleaningSlots.name: numCleaningSlots
numCleaningSlots.description: Returns the number of storage slots reserved for cleaning media of this domain. When set, the value is the total number of slots to reserve for cleaning media of this domain. The library will reserve a set of storage segments such that total number of storage slots is greater than or equal to numCleaningSlots.

numDriveElements.name: numDriveElements
numDriveElements.description: Number of drives for this media type.

phFrameTable.name: phFrameTable
phFrameTable.description: ** This table is optional ** This is a list of all the frames in the library.

phFrameType.name: phFrameType
phFrameType.description: ** This object is optional ** Physical type of frame. Only controlModule(6) and expansionModule(7) values are actually valid for the frame type.

phFrameSerialNumber.name: phFrameSerialNumber
phFrameSerialNumber.description: ** This object is optional ** Serial number of this frame, if available.

phFrameNumRacks.name: phFrameNumRacks
phFrameNumRacks.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of racks in this frame.

phSegmentTable.name: phSegmentTable
phSegmentTable.description: This is a list of all the segments in the library.

phSegmentAisle.name: phSegmentAisle
phSegmentAisle.description: Aisle coordinate value for this segment.

phSegmentFrame.name: phSegmentFrame
phSegmentFrame.description: Frame coordinate value for this segment.

phSegmentRack.name: phSegmentRack
phSegmentRack.description: Rack coordinate value for this segment.

phSegmentCol.name: phSegmentCol
phSegmentCol.description: Column coordinate value for this segment.

phSegmentStartingRow.name: phSegmentStartingRow
phSegmentStartingRow.description: Row coordinate of the first element in this segment. This is useful to divide a column into multiple segments. For instance, a segment which contains rows 1 - 10 would have phSegmentStartingRow = 1. A segment which contains rows 11 - 20 in the same column would have phSegmentStartingRow = 11.

phSegmentSize.name: phSegmentSize
phSegmentSize.description: Number of elements in this segment.

phSegmentType.name: phSegmentType
phSegmentType.description: This segment's type (storage, drive, I/E, etc.).

phSegmentMediaDomain.name: phSegmentMediaDomain
phSegmentMediaDomain.description: Element domain of this segment. Points a row in the media domain table.

phSegmentStatus.name: phSegmentStatus
phSegmentStatus.description: Status of this segment. May be installed, not installed, or reserved for use by the automatic cleaning service.

phSegmentCodStatus.name: phSegmentCodStatus
phSegmentCodStatus.description: Capacity on Demand (COD) status for this segment. noCod means that COD is not enabled for this library.

phSegStartingAddress.name: phSegStartingAddress
phSegStartingAddress.description: SCSI media changer element address of the first row in this segment. Element addresses are contiguous, so we can derive the address of each row in the segment from the address of the first row.

phStorageSegTable.name: phStorageSegTable
phStorageSegTable.description: This is a list of all the storage segments in the library, indexed by their media domain and segment Index.

phStorageSegSize.name: phStorageSegSize
phStorageSegSize.description: Number of elements in this segment.

phIeSegTable.name: phIeSegTable
phIeSegTable.description: ** Some objects in this table are optional ** This is a list of all the I/E segments in the library, indexed by their media domain and segment index.

phIeSegEntry.name: phIeSegEntry
phIeSegEntry.description: ** Some objects in this entry are optional **

phIeSegSize.name: phIeSegSize
phIeSegSize.description: Number of elements in this segment.

phIeSegReserve.name: phIeSegReserve
phIeSegReserve.description: ** This object is optional ** Mechanism to release and reserve this I/E segment.

phIeSegReservedBy.name: phIeSegReservedBy
phIeSegReservedBy.description: ** This object is optional ** Indicator of who reserved this I/E segment.

phIeSegOnlineStatus.name: phIeSegOnlineStatus
phIeSegOnlineStatus.description: ** This object is optional ** Takes this I/E segment online/offline.

phIeSegCommand.name: phIeSegCommand
phIeSegCommand.description: ** This object is optional ** Issue a command to this I/E station.

phIeStationTable.name: phIeStationTable
phIeStationTable.description: This is a list of all the I/E stations in the library

phIeStationNumber.name: phIeStationNumber
phIeStationNumber.description: Index of I/E station within a frame. If a frame has N I/E stations, the range of phIeStationNumber is 1 through N.

phIeStationDoorStatus.name: phIeStationDoorStatus
phIeStationDoorStatus.description: Is the station door open/closed, locked/unlocked ?

phIeStationREDId.name: phIeStationREDId
phIeStationREDId.description: Runtime Error Detection identifier for this import/export station.

phDriveSegTable.name: phDriveSegTable
phDriveSegTable.description: This is a list of all the drive segments in the library, indexed by their media domain, media type and segment index.

phDriveSegSize.name: phDriveSegSize
phDriveSegSize.description: Number of drive elements in this segment.

phDriveSegMediaType.name: phDriveSegMediaType
phDriveSegMediaType.description: Exact media type of this segment. With phSegmentMediaDomain, points a row in the media type table.

phDriveSegInterfaceType.name: phDriveSegInterfaceType
phDriveSegInterfaceType.description: Data interface type of this segment.

phCleaningSegTable.name: phCleaningSegTable
phCleaningSegTable.description: ** This table is optional ** This is a list of all the storage segments in the library which have been reserved for use by automatic cleaning services.

phCleaningSegSize.name: phCleaningSegSize
phCleaningSegSize.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of elements in this segment.

phCleaningSegRowStatus.name: phCleaningSegRowStatus
phCleaningSegRowStatus.description: ** This object is optional ** Management application use this object to to reserve segment for cleaning or release the segment for use as storage.

phStorageRow.name: phStorageRow
phStorageRow.description: ** This object is optional ** Row coordinate value for this storage slot.

phStorageElementAddr.name: phStorageElementAddr
phStorageElementAddr.description: ** This object is optional ** SCSI Medium Changer Element Address for this storage slot.

phIeRow.name: phIeRow
phIeRow.description: ** This object is optional ** Row coordinate value for this I/E slot

phIeElementAddr.name: phIeElementAddr
phIeElementAddr.description: ** This object is optional ** SCSI Medium Changer Element Address for this I/E slot.

phIeMediaPresent.name: phIeMediaPresent
phIeMediaPresent.description: ** This object is optional ** Is a media cartridge present in this slot? Values are: yes(1) - system is certain that a cartridge is present. no(2) - system is certain that a cartridge is not present. error(3) - an error ocurred while determining if media is present.

phIeMediaId.name: phIeMediaId
phIeMediaId.description: ** This object is optional ** Media ID bar code of cartridge in this I/E slot, if present and available. Returns zero length string if the bar code is not available for any reason.

phDriveRow.name: phDriveRow
phDriveRow.description: Row coordinate value for this drive element.

phDriveElementAddr.name: phDriveElementAddr
phDriveElementAddr.description: SCSI Element Address for this drive element.

phDriveWwn.name: phDriveWwn
phDriveWwn.description: World Wide Node Name for this drive.

phDriveVendor.name: phDriveVendor
phDriveVendor.description: Name of the vendor of this drive.

phDriveAutoCleaning.name: phDriveAutoCleaning
phDriveAutoCleaning.description: Add or remove this drive from automatic cleaning list.

phDriveInterfaceType.name: phDriveInterfaceType
phDriveInterfaceType.description: Data interface type (SCSI, Fibre Channel, etc.).

phDriveFcLoopId.name: phDriveFcLoopId
phDriveFcLoopId.description: Loop ID for Fibre Channel interface drives, undefined for other interface type drives.

phDriveFcLoopIdMode.name: phDriveFcLoopIdMode
phDriveFcLoopIdMode.description: Loop ID Mode for Fibre Channel interface drives, undefined for other interface type drives. Controls negotiation of the port ID on the Fibre Channel connection.

phDriveFcHardId.name: phDriveFcHardId
phDriveFcHardId.description: Preferred port ID Mode for Fibre Channel interface drives, undefined for other interface type drives. Used only when port ID mode is set to 'hard'.

phDriveCommand.name: phDriveCommand
phDriveCommand.description: Perform various operations on a drive: *************************************** online(1) - bring drive online offline(2) - take drive offline reset(3) - perform a warm reset powerOn(4) - perform power on powerOff(5) - peform power off powerCycle(6) - perform power cycle driveBrickUpdate(7) - download firmware to the drive brick

phDriveFcPortId.name: phDriveFcPortId
phDriveFcPortId.description: Port ID for fabric attached Fibre Channel drives, undefined for other interface type drives.

phDriveCompressionOn.name: phDriveCompressionOn
phDriveCompressionOn.description: Is compression turned on for this drive?

phDriveWriteProtected.name: phDriveWriteProtected
phDriveWriteProtected.description: Is write protection turned on for this drive?

phDriveNumLoads.name: phDriveNumLoads
phDriveNumLoads.description: Total number of loads for this drive. Count is for the entire lifetime of the drive.

phDriveNumCleans.name: phDriveNumCleans
phDriveNumCleans.description: Total number of cleaning operations peroformed on this drive. Count is for the entire lifetime of the drive.

phDriveReadErrors.name: phDriveReadErrors
phDriveReadErrors.description: Number of read errors for this drive. Count is for the entire lifetime of the drive.

phDriveWriteErrors.name: phDriveWriteErrors
phDriveWriteErrors.description: Number of write errors for this drive. Count is for the entire lifetime of the drive.

phDriveMbytesRead.name: phDriveMbytesRead
phDriveMbytesRead.description: Number of megabytes of data read from this drive.

phDriveMbytesWritten.name: phDriveMbytesWritten
phDriveMbytesWritten.description: Number of megabytes of data written to this drive.

phDriveREDId.name: phDriveREDId
phDriveREDId.description: Runtime Error Detection identifier for this tape drive.

phDriveOnlineStatus.name: phDriveOnlineStatus
phDriveOnlineStatus.description: Returns either online(1) or offline(2). The shutdown(3) state is not applicable to this object. To change the online state of the drive, set the phDriveCommand object to online(1) or offline(2).

phDriveErrorCodeBytes.name: phDriveErrorCodeBytes
phDriveErrorCodeBytes.description: String of bytes which contains error information about the drive. The meaning of each byte is as follows: ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ byte 0: drive seven segment display code

phDriveRasStatus.name: phDriveRasStatus
phDriveRasStatus.description: RAS status for this individual drive.

phDriveWwPortName.name: phDriveWwPortName
phDriveWwPortName.description: World Wide Port Name for this drive.

phDriveStatHistoryTable.name: phDriveStatHistoryTable
phDriveStatHistoryTable.description: This table contains historical data on drive operations. Each row in the table gives various statistical data for a single drive over a one hour period. The table is indexed such that phIndex = 0 is the current hour's data, phIndex = 1 is one hour ago, phIndex = 2 is two hours ago, etc.

phHourIndex.name: phHourIndex
phHourIndex.description: Index into the historical data. The integer value is the number in the past the data the data was collected. For example, phHourIndex = 0 means the current hour's statistics, phHourIndex = 1 means one hour in the past, phHourIndex = 2 means two hours in the past.

phHourlyMBytesRead.name: phHourlyMBytesRead
phHourlyMBytesRead.description: Number of megabytes read by this drive during the one hour period indicated by phHourIndex.

phHourlyMBytesWritten.name: phHourlyMBytesWritten
phHourlyMBytesWritten.description: Number of megabytes written by this drive during the one hour period indicated by phHourIndex.

phHourlyMounts.name: phHourlyMounts
phHourlyMounts.description: Number of mounts performed by this drive during the one hour period indicated by phHourIndex.

fcDrivePortTable.name: fcDrivePortTable
fcDrivePortTable.description: This table contains objects pertaining to Fibre Channel port settings on native Fibre Channel drives.

fcDrivePortEntry.name: fcDrivePortEntry
fcDrivePortEntry.description: A row object describing a Fibre Channel port.

fcPortPreferredSpeed.name: fcPortPreferredSpeed
fcPortPreferredSpeed.description: Preferred transmitter speed. Except for auto(1), the numerical value of this object is equal to the port speed in megabits per second. ******************************************* auto(1) - speed is auto-negotiated with no preferred speed megabits1000(1000) - 1000 megabits per second megabits2000(2000) - 2000 megabits per second

fcPortNegotiatedSpeed.name: fcPortNegotiatedSpeed
fcPortNegotiatedSpeed.description: Actual transmitter speed as negotiated on the FC network. The numerical value of this object is equal to the port speed in megabits per second. Although auto(1) is defined in the AdicFcPortSpeed enumeration, the fcPortNegotiatedSpeed should never return this value. ******************************************* auto(1) - This object should never auto(1) megabits1000(1000) - 1000 megabits per second megabits2000(2000) - 2000 megabits per second

fcPortPreferredType.name: fcPortPreferredType
fcPortPreferredType.description: Preferred port type, such as N_Port or NL_Port. auto(1) means no preference, auto-negotiate.

fcPortNegotiatedType.name: fcPortNegotiatedType
fcPortNegotiatedType.description: Actual port type as negotiated on the FC network. Should never return auto(1).

fcPortTypeQualifier.name: fcPortTypeQualifier
fcPortTypeQualifier.description: Is this a public or private port?

phMediaElementAddress.name: phMediaElementAddress
phMediaElementAddress.description: Element address where this cartridge is physically located.

phMediaMounts.name: phMediaMounts
phMediaMounts.description: Number of times this cartridge has been mounted.

phMediaReadErrors.name: phMediaReadErrors
phMediaReadErrors.description: Number of errors when reading from this cartridge.

phMediaWriteErrors.name: phMediaWriteErrors
phMediaWriteErrors.description: Number of errors when writing to this cartridge.

phMediaCapacity.name: phMediaCapacity
phMediaCapacity.description: Capacity of this cartridge in megabytes. Returns -1 if capacity is unknown.

phMediaFreeSpace.name: phMediaFreeSpace
phMediaFreeSpace.description: Amount of free space on this cartridge in megabytes. Returns -1 if free space is unknown.

phMediaExported.name: phMediaExported
phMediaExported.description: Has this cartridge been exported from the library?

phMediaImportTimestamp.name: phMediaImportTimestamp
phMediaImportTimestamp.description: Timestamp when cartridge was imported. Compatible with the SMIv2 DateAndTime textual convention. Encode is as follows: field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 1992-5-26,13:30:15.0,-4:0 Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

phMediaExportTimestamp.name: phMediaExportTimestamp
phMediaExportTimestamp.description: Timestamp when cartridge was exported. Compatible with the SMIv2 DateAndTime textual convention. Encode is as follows: field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 1992-5-26,13:30:15.0,-4:0 Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

phTransportNumRecoveredGets.name: phTransportNumRecoveredGets
phTransportNumRecoveredGets.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered get operations for this transport element. The count is for the entire lifetime of the library.

phTransportNumRecoveredPuts.name: phTransportNumRecoveredPuts
phTransportNumRecoveredPuts.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered put operations for this transport element. The count is for the entire lifetime of the library.

phTransportNumRecoveredScans.name: phTransportNumRecoveredScans
phTransportNumRecoveredScans.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered scan operations for this transport element. The count is for the entire lifetime of the library.

phTransportNumPuts.name: phTransportNumPuts
phTransportNumPuts.description: ** This object is optional ** Number put operations for this transport element. The count is for the entire lifetime of the library.

phTransportREDId.name: phTransportREDId
phTransportREDId.description: ** This object is optional ** Runtime Error Detection identifier for this tape drive.

phCleaningMediaTable.name: phCleaningMediaTable
phCleaningMediaTable.description: ** This table is optional ** This is a combination of data about slots reserved for automatic cleaning and the cleaning cartridges themselves. Since the relationship between slots and cartridges is one-to-one, we can combine these data.

phCleaningMediaStatus.name: phCleaningMediaStatus
phCleaningMediaStatus.description: ** This object is optional ** Cleaning storage is allocated by segment; the value of phCleaningMediaStatus indicates if the slot is being used to store a cartridge or not. allocated(1) means this slot is home to cartridge. unallocated(2) means there is no cartridge associated with this slot.

phCleaningMediaTypeIndex.name: phCleaningMediaTypeIndex
phCleaningMediaTypeIndex.description: ** This object is optional ** Exact media type of this cleaning cartridge. Value points to a row in the Media Type table with mediaTypeIndex = phCleaningMediaTypeIndex.

phCleaningMediaVendorId.name: phCleaningMediaVendorId
phCleaningMediaVendorId.description: ** This object is optional ** Vendor of drives that this cleaning cartridge is designed to clean. Value points to a row in the Vendor table with vendorIdIndex = phCleaningMediaVendorId.

phCleaningMediaBarcode.name: phCleaningMediaBarcode
phCleaningMediaBarcode.description: ** This object is optional ** Barcode (if present).

phCleaningMediaUseCount.name: phCleaningMediaUseCount
phCleaningMediaUseCount.description: ** This object is optional ** Use count. May be set to any value to accomodate importing cartridges that have already been used.

phCleaningMediaMaxUses.name: phCleaningMediaMaxUses
phCleaningMediaMaxUses.description: ** This object is optional ** Maximum number of uses for this cartidge.

phCleaningMediaImportTimestamp.name: phCleaningMediaImportTimestamp
phCleaningMediaImportTimestamp.description: ** This object is optional ** Timestamp when this cartridge was imported. Compatible with the SMIv2 DateAndTime textual convention. Encode is as follows: field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 1992-5-26,13:30:15.0,-4:0 Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

loGeneralInfoTable.name: loGeneralInfoTable
loGeneralInfoTable.description: General information about the Logical Library Manager.

maxLogicalLibraries.name: maxLogicalLibraries
maxLogicalLibraries.description: Maximum number of logical libraries. This includes all media types.

numLogicalLibraries.name: numLogicalLibraries
numLogicalLibraries.description: Current number of logical libraries configured. This includes all media types.

autoPartitionTable.name: autoPartitionTable
autoPartitionTable.description: Variables pertaining to library auto partitioning.

autoPartitionEntry.name: autoPartitionEntry
autoPartitionEntry.description: Autopartitioning is based on the media domain, media type, and drive data port interface type.

numAutoPartition.name: numAutoPartition
numAutoPartition.description: Number of partitions to create upon automatic partitioning for a given media domain, media type and interface type.

autoPartitionCommand.name: autoPartitionCommand
autoPartitionCommand.description: Perform operation based on the media domain, media type, and interface type: autoPartition(1) - create the number of partitions indicated by the numAutoPartition object, with the library resouces divided equally among the partitions.

productIdTable.name: productIdTable
productIdTable.description: Table of possible product names and configuration constraints.

logicalLibraryIndex.name: logicalLibraryIndex
logicalLibraryIndex.description: Identifies the Logical Library to be managed.

assignedLun.name: assignedLun
assignedLun.description: Assigned LUN of this library's (virtual) SCSI media changer. This can only be changed through the SANMgr proxy MIB device map table.

mediaDomain.name: mediaDomain
mediaDomain.description: Points to entry in the Physical Library MediaDomainTable.

mediaType.name: mediaType
mediaType.description: Points to entry in the Physical Library MediaTypeTable.

automaticCleaning.name: automaticCleaning
automaticCleaning.description: Enables/Disables automatic cleaning for drives this logical library.

mediaTypeChecking.name: mediaTypeChecking
mediaTypeChecking.description: Enables/Disables media type checking for this logical library.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: Serial Number of this logical library. Assigned by MCB when logical library is created.

loInterfaceType.name: loInterfaceType
loInterfaceType.description: Type of data interface for this logical library.

loNumLibraries.name: loNumLibraries
loNumLibraries.description: Formerly used in auto partition operation. Made obsolete by autoPartition table.

loLtoTapeTags.name: loLtoTapeTags
loLtoTapeTags.description: Controls the inclusion of media type characters in the media barcodes for this logical library. For example, the LTO media type characters are 'L1' for LTO-1 and 'L2' for LTO-2. This object applies to logical libraries of all media domains, not just LTO (as the name suggests).

loMediaTypeCheckingPolicy.name: loMediaTypeCheckingPolicy
loMediaTypeCheckingPolicy.description: Allows the user to specify special handling of media type information in barcodes. Values are: 0 - media type checking disabled; media type as derived from barcode is irrelevant. 911 - 'required'; barcode MUST be a valid ADIC barcode, the correct media type may be derived from the barcode using the ADIC algorithm. Other - 'override'; the media type may not be derived from the barcode, use this value instead. The value map is the same as the mediaTypeIndex variable: the logical library's mediaDomain variable specifies the media domain and loMediaTypeCheckingPolicy specifies the media type that will be assumed for all media in this logical library.

loSegmentTable.name: loSegmentTable
loSegmentTable.description: This is a list of all the segments in the library.

loSegmentAisle.name: loSegmentAisle
loSegmentAisle.description: Aisle coordinate value for this segment.

loSegmentFrame.name: loSegmentFrame
loSegmentFrame.description: Frame coordinate value for this segment.

loSegmentRack.name: loSegmentRack
loSegmentRack.description: Rack coordinate value for this segment.

loSegmentCol.name: loSegmentCol
loSegmentCol.description: Column coordinate value for this segment.

loSegmentStartingRow.name: loSegmentStartingRow
loSegmentStartingRow.description: Row coordinate of the first element in this segment. This is useful to divide a column into multiple segments. For instance, a segment which contains rows 1 - 10 would have loSegmentStartingRow = 1. A segment which contains rows 11 - 20 in the same column would have loSegmentStartingRow = 11.

loSegmentSize.name: loSegmentSize
loSegmentSize.description: Number of elements in this segment.

loSegmentMediaDomain.name: loSegmentMediaDomain
loSegmentMediaDomain.description: Media domain for this segment. Points to a row in the media domain table.

loSegmentBelongsTo.name: loSegmentBelongsTo
loSegmentBelongsTo.description: logicalLibraryIndex to which this segment is allocated. This object has no meaning for an I/E segment since I/E segments may be shared. For I/E segments, the list of logical libaraies which share the segment may be found in the loSegmentAssignmentTable.

loSegmentCommand.name: loSegmentCommand
loSegmentCommand.description: Operation to perform using objects in varbind list.

loSegmentStatus.name: loSegmentStatus
loSegmentStatus.description: Is this segment allocated to a logical library?

loSegmentStartingAddress.name: loSegmentStartingAddress
loSegmentStartingAddress.description: Logical SCSI element address of the first element (row) in this segment. Element addresses are contiguous within a segment and unique within a logical library.

loSegmentBelongsToTable.name: loSegmentBelongsToTable
loSegmentBelongsToTable.description: This is a list of the logical libraries to which each segments belongs. Storage and drive segments belong to a maximum of one logical library, but I/E segments may be shared among several logical libraries.

loSegmentAssignedTo.name: loSegmentAssignedTo
loSegmentAssignedTo.description: logicalLibraryIndex to which this segment belongs.

loStorageSegTable.name: loStorageSegTable
loStorageSegTable.description: This is a list of all the storage segments in the library, indexed by a flat segment index loStorageSegIndex.

loStorageSegSize.name: loStorageSegSize
loStorageSegSize.description: Number of storage elements in this segment.

loStorageSegStartingAddress.name: loStorageSegStartingAddress
loStorageSegStartingAddress.description: Logical SCSI element address of the first element (row) in this storage segment. Element addresses are contiguous within a segment and unique within a logical library.

loIeSegTable.name: loIeSegTable
loIeSegTable.description: This is a list of all the I/E segments in the logical library, indexed by a flat segment index.

loIeSegSize.name: loIeSegSize
loIeSegSize.description: Number of I/E elements in this segment.

loIeSegReserve.name: loIeSegReserve
loIeSegReserve.description: Mechanism to release and reserve this I/E segment.

loIeSegReservedBy.name: loIeSegReservedBy
loIeSegReservedBy.description: Index of logical library for which this I/E segment has been reserved.

loIeSegStartingAddress.name: loIeSegStartingAddress
loIeSegStartingAddress.description: Logical SCSI element address of the first element (row) in this I/E segment. Element addresses are contiguous within a segment and unique within a logical library.

loDriveSegTable.name: loDriveSegTable
loDriveSegTable.description: This is a list of all the drive segments in the library, indexed by their media domain, media type and segment index.

loDriveSegSize.name: loDriveSegSize
loDriveSegSize.description: Number of elements in this segment.

loDriveSegStartingAddress.name: loDriveSegStartingAddress
loDriveSegStartingAddress.description: Logical SCSI element address of the first element (row) in this drive segment. Element addresses are contiguous within a segment and unique within a logical library.

loDriveSegMediaType.name: loDriveSegMediaType
loDriveSegMediaType.description: Exact media type of this segment. With loSegmentMediaDomain, points a row in the media type table.

loStorageRow.name: loStorageRow
loStorageRow.description: Row coordinate value for this storage slot.

loIeRow.name: loIeRow
loIeRow.description: Row coordinate value for this storage slot.

loDriveRow.name: loDriveRow
loDriveRow.description: Row coordinate value for where this drive element is physically located.

loStatisticsTable.name: loStatisticsTable
loStatisticsTable.description: ** This table is optional ** Table of statistics for each logical library. Error counts, recovery counts, etc. .

loNumRecoveredGets.name: loNumRecoveredGets
loNumRecoveredGets.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered get operations for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loNumRecoveredPuts.name: loNumRecoveredPuts
loNumRecoveredPuts.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered putt operations for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loNumRecoveredScans.name: loNumRecoveredScans
loNumRecoveredScans.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of recovered scan operations for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loStatsNumPuts.name: loStatsNumPuts
loStatsNumPuts.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of put operations performed for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loStatsNumPutRetries.name: loStatsNumPutRetries
loStatsNumPutRetries.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of retried put operations performed for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loStatsNumGetRetries.name: loStatsNumGetRetries
loStatsNumGetRetries.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of retried get operations performed for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

loStatsNumScanRetries.name: loStatsNumScanRetries
loStatsNumScanRetries.description: ** This object is optional ** Number of retried scan operations performed for this logical library. The count is for the entire lifetime of the logical library.

rasSystemStatusTable.name: rasSystemStatusTable
rasSystemStatusTable.description: Contains status information for various system status groups.

rasSystemStatusEntry.name: rasSystemStatusEntry
rasSystemStatusEntry.description: Information for a particular system status group. The componentId index refers to the MCB through which the management application accesses the RAS manager. The rasStatusGroupIndex specifies the system status group for which the entry contains information.

rasStatusGroupIndex.name: rasStatusGroupIndex
rasStatusGroupIndex.description: Identifies the system status group for which this row object contains information.

rasStatusGroupStatus.name: rasStatusGroupStatus
rasStatusGroupStatus.description: The status (or condition) of this system status group. Use of the 'indeterminate' state: 'indeterminate' is primarily for use in the rasStatusGroupPreviousStatus object, where there may not be any previous state information.

rasStatusGroupPreviousStatus.name: rasStatusGroupPreviousStatus
rasStatusGroupPreviousStatus.description: After a state change, this object gives the previous state of the system status group. If there is no previous state information available, such as when resetting the system, the previous state is 'indeterminate'.

rasStatusGroupTextSummary.name: rasStatusGroupTextSummary
rasStatusGroupTextSummary.description: A brief message describing the state of this system status group. If the rasStatusGroupStatus is other than 'good', this object should return the reason why this is so.

rasStatusGroupTotalTickets.name: rasStatusGroupTotalTickets
rasStatusGroupTotalTickets.description: The total number of RAS tickets created against this system status group.

rasStatusGroupOpenTickets.name: rasStatusGroupOpenTickets
rasStatusGroupOpenTickets.description: The number of RAS tickets currently open against this system status group.

rasStatusGroupActionsPending.name: rasStatusGroupActionsPending
rasStatusGroupActionsPending.description: The number of actions pending against this system status group.

rasStatusGroupLastChange.name: rasStatusGroupLastChange
rasStatusGroupLastChange.description: Timestamp of the last time the status changed.

rasTicketTable.name: rasTicketTable
rasTicketTable.description: Contains one row for each ticket in the database.

rasTicketEntry.name: rasTicketEntry
rasTicketEntry.description: Each entry contains information for a single RAS ticket. The componentId index refers to the MCB through which the management application accesses the RAS manager. The rasTicketId specifies the ticket instance.

rasTicketId.name: rasTicketId
rasTicketId.description: Unique identifier for this ticket. The RAS system defines the ticket ID as an unsigned 32 bit integer, so it is declared here as a Guage32.

rasTicketRowStatus.name: rasTicketRowStatus
rasTicketRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of rows in this table. Creation of RAS tickets via SNMP is currently not permitted, so writing a value of createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5) does not create a new row; it may return error indication.

rasTicketStatusGroup.name: rasTicketStatusGroup
rasTicketStatusGroup.description: System status group to which this ticket belongs.

rasTicketGroupStatus.name: rasTicketGroupStatus
rasTicketGroupStatus.description: Status determination that this ticket indicates against its system status group.

rasTicketTimeOpened.name: rasTicketTimeOpened
rasTicketTimeOpened.description: Date and time when ticket was opened.

rasTicketTimeClosed.name: rasTicketTimeClosed
rasTicketTimeClosed.description: Date and time when ticket was closed.

rasTicketCount.name: rasTicketCount
rasTicketCount.description: Number of times an attempt was made to open a duplicate ticket.

rasTicketKeyReport.name: rasTicketKeyReport
rasTicketKeyReport.description: Contains 0 or a valid rasReportId value. Indicates which report is currently responsible for the severity of the ticket.

rasReportTable.name: rasReportTable
rasReportTable.description: Contains one row for each ticket/report combination in the database. The table is indexed off the RAS Ticket Table, it may contain many RAS Report entries for a single RAS Ticket.

rasReportEntry.name: rasReportEntry
rasReportEntry.description: Each entry contains information for a single RAS Report.

rasReportId.name: rasReportId
rasReportId.description: Identifies the RAS Report for which this this row object contains information. The RAS system defines the report ID as an unsigned 32 bit integer, so it is declared here as a Guage32.

rasReportRowStatus.name: rasReportRowStatus
rasReportRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of rows in the RAS Report table.

rasReportTimestamp.name: rasReportTimestamp
rasReportTimestamp.description: Time when this event was generated.

rasReportStatusGroup.name: rasReportStatusGroup
rasReportStatusGroup.description: The subsystem that is reporting the event.

rasReportOrcData.name: rasReportOrcData
rasReportOrcData.description: Event payload generated by the reporting subsystem.

rasReportGroupStatus.name: rasReportGroupStatus
rasReportGroupStatus.description: Status determination that this report indicates against the specific FRU.

rasReportOrcDescription.name: rasReportOrcDescription
rasReportOrcDescription.description: Description of the operation result code.

rasReportRepeatCounter.name: rasReportRepeatCounter
rasReportRepeatCounter.description: Number of times an identical report has been generated.

rasReportHeadReport.name: rasReportHeadReport
rasReportHeadReport.description: The head report field allows reports to be sorted according to FRU branch.

rasFruStatTable.name: rasFruStatTable
rasFruStatTable.description: Each row dsecribes the history and RAS statistics for a single FRU.

rasFruStatEntry.name: rasFruStatEntry
rasFruStatEntry.description: Each entry contains information for a single FRU.

rasFruStatIndex.name: rasFruStatIndex
rasFruStatIndex.description: Flat index for the FRU statistics table.

rasFruStatStatusGroup.name: rasFruStatStatusGroup
rasFruStatStatusGroup.description: Status group to which this FRU belongs.

rasFruStatFruCategory.name: rasFruStatFruCategory
rasFruStatFruCategory.description: Category to which this FRU belongs.

rasFruStatFirstReportTime.name: rasFruStatFirstReportTime
rasFruStatFirstReportTime.description: Time when the first RAS report was generated for this FRU.

rasFruStatLastReportTime.name: rasFruStatLastReportTime
rasFruStatLastReportTime.description: Time when the most recent RAS report was generated for this FRU.

rasFruStatTotalTickets.name: rasFruStatTotalTickets
rasFruStatTotalTickets.description: Total number of RAS tickets created against this FRU, both open and closed tickets.

rasFruStatOpenTickets.name: rasFruStatOpenTickets
rasFruStatOpenTickets.description: Number of RAS tickets currently open against this FRU.

rasFruStatSerialNumber.name: rasFruStatSerialNumber
rasFruStatSerialNumber.description: The unique serial number of the FRU.

rasFruStatState.name: rasFruStatState
rasFruStatState.description: State = current(1) indicates that the FRU is currently installed. State = old(2) indicates that the FRU has been removed and the data is historic.

rasTicketFilterTable.name: rasTicketFilterTable
rasTicketFilterTable.description: Contains filter settings for ticket table walking. Only those rows which match the filter criteria will appear in the RAS ticket table when traversed using GetNext or GetBulk.

rasTicketFilterStatusGroup.name: rasTicketFilterStatusGroup
rasTicketFilterStatusGroup.description: Identifies the system status group for which tickets will be returned.

rasTicketFilterState.name: rasTicketFilterState
rasTicketFilterState.description: Identifies the ticket state (open, closed, etc.) for which tickets will be returned.

rasTicketFilterSeverity.name: rasTicketFilterSeverity
rasTicketFilterSeverity.description: Identifies the ticket severity for which tickets will be returned. ========================================= high: Tickets/reports with status 'failed' only. medium: Tickets/reports with status 'failed' or 'warning'. low: All tickets/reports.

moveMediaComplete.name: moveMediaComplete
moveMediaComplete.description: A piece of media has been move from one location to another. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) phStorageElementAddr - source element address phStorageElementAddr - destination element address

tapeDriveAdded.name: tapeDriveAdded
tapeDriveAdded.description: A tape drive was added to the library. This trap is issued when a tape drive previously unknown to the library becomes known. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) phDriveRow - row component of the drive's physical location in the library.

tapeDriveRemoved.name: tapeDriveRemoved
tapeDriveRemoved.description: A tape drive was removed from the library. This trap is issued when a tape drive is removed from library's configuration. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) phDriveRow - row component of the drive's physical location in the library.

mediaMounted.name: mediaMounted
mediaMounted.description: Media was mounted in the tape drive indicated in the trap payload. This trap is issued upon every mount operation. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) phDriveRow - row component of the drive's physical location in the library.

mediaDismounted.name: mediaDismounted
mediaDismounted.description: Media was dismounted in the tape drive indicated in the trap payload. This trap is issued upon every dismount operation. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) phDriveRow - row component of the drive's physical location in the library. phDriveMbytesRead - over lifetime of drive phDriveMbytesWritten - over lifetime of drive

ieStationInventoryPerformed.name: ieStationInventoryPerformed
ieStationInventoryPerformed.description: An inventory operation has been performed on an I/E station.

rcuReady.name: rcuReady
rcuReady.description: The RCU indicated in the payload has transitioned from the NotReady state to the Ready state.

rcuNotReady.name: rcuNotReady
rcuNotReady.description: The RCU indicated in the payload has transitioned from the NotReady state to the Ready state.

driveActivityUpdate.name: driveActivityUpdate
driveActivityUpdate.description: Drive activity integrated over a fixed time period. Currently, the time period is one hour. NOTE: the drive is identified by the instance OID contained in the phHourlyMBytesRead, phHourlyMBytesWritten, and phHourlyWritten varbinds.

driveBrickFwUpdateSuccess.name: driveBrickFwUpdateSuccess
driveBrickFwUpdateSuccess.description: Drive brick's firmware was successfully updated. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) trapSummaryText - brief message about the update phDriveSerialNumber - the drive serial number. The OID of the varbind encoded in the trap payload must be the full OID, column OID plus indices. phDriveFirmwareVersion - the drive firmware version identifier. The OID of the varbind encoded in the trap payload must be the full OID, column OID plus indices.

driveBrickFwUpdateFailure.name: driveBrickFwUpdateFailure
driveBrickFwUpdateFailure.description: Attempt to update drive brick's firmware has failed. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) trapSummaryText - brief message about the update phDriveSerialNumber - the drive serial number. The OID of the varbind encoded in the trap payload must be the full OID, column OID plus indices. phDriveFirmwareVersion - the drive firmware version identifier. The OID of the varbind encoded in the trap payload must be the full OID, column OID plus indices.

physLibraryConfigurationChange.name: physLibraryConfigurationChange
physLibraryConfigurationChange.description: The physical configuration of the library has been changed, possibly invalidating the data in the management application's model. For example, an LTO magazine swapped for a DLT magazine. The management application should repopulate its data model.

physLibraryRESChange.name: physLibraryRESChange
physLibraryRESChange.description: The physical library managers issues this trap when it detects that the Read Element Status data has changed. This generally occurs after an inventory. The range of elements specified by the last two varbinds may represent storage drive, or I/E elements.

driveBrickFwUpdateStart.name: driveBrickFwUpdateStart
driveBrickFwUpdateStart.description: Drive brick firmware update has started. componentId - identifies MCB trapSequenceNumber - generic sequence number trapSeverity - should be informational(5) trapSummaryText - brief message about the update phDriveSerialNumber - the drive serial number. The OID of the varbind encoded in the trap payload must be the full OID, column OID plus indices.

connectivityGroupStatusChange.name: connectivityGroupStatusChange
connectivityGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the connectivity system status group has changed. The present state of the connectivity status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

controlGroupStatusChange.name: controlGroupStatusChange
controlGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the control system status group has changed. The present state of the control status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

coolingGroupStatusChange.name: coolingGroupStatusChange
coolingGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the cooling system status group has changed. The present state of the cooling status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

drivesAndMediaGroupStatusChange.name: drivesAndMediaGroupStatusChange
drivesAndMediaGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the drives and media system status group has changed. The present state of the drives and media status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

powerGroupStatusChange.name: powerGroupStatusChange
powerGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the power system status group has changed. The present state of the power status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

roboticsGroupStatusChange.name: roboticsGroupStatusChange
roboticsGroupStatusChange.description: The overall state of the robotics system status group has changed. The present state of the robotics status group is given by the value of the rasStatusGroupStatus object in the trap payload.

rasEventNotification.name: rasEventNotification
rasEventNotification.description: A RAS event has occurred, possibly requiring action by the management application.

logRetrievalComplete.name: logRetrievalComplete
logRetrievalComplete.description: Indicates that the system has retrieved all remote log files as part of the capture snapshot procedure.
